text: Teng Chia-chi (; born 24 May 1956) is a Taiwanese politician. ==Education== Teng obtained his bachelor's and master's degree in civil engineering from National Cheng Kung University and doctoral degree in environmental engineering from the University of California, Los Angeles in the United States. ==Political careers== Teng is currently the Deputy Mayor of Taipei since 25 December 2014. ==References== Category:1956 births Category:Living people Category:Deputy mayors of Taipei Category:National Cheng Kung University alumni Category:University of California, Los Angeles alumni Category:21st-century Taiwanese politicians Category:20th-century Taiwanese politicians Category:Taipei City Councilors
